The paper discusses the issue of identifying influential bloggers, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves natural language processing and text analysis, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of metrics to score blog posts, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of blogging on the masses, which could fall under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Finally, the paper discusses the temporal aspects of blogging, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
